Q. Order-agnostic binary search means ?
a binary search that works on both ascending and descending sorted arrays â€” without knowing the order in advance.
âš™ï¸ Steps :
         Check first and last element
                            - If first < last â†’ array is ascending
                            - Else â†’ array is descending
         Then use binary search rules for that order.

